===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|boy}}, {{m|enm|boye|t=servant, commoner, knave, boy}}, from {{inh|en|ang|bōia|t=boy}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*bōjô|t=younger brother, young male relation}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*bō-|t=brother, close male relation}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰā-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*bʰāt-|t=father, elder brother, brother}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|boy||boy}}, {{cog|fy|boai||boy}}, {{cog|dum|boi}}, {{m|dum|booi||boy}}, {{cog|nds|Boi||boy}}, and probably to the {{etyl|ang|-}} proper name ''Bōia''. Also related to {{cog|vls|boe||brother}}, {{etyl|no|-}} dialectal {{m|no|boa||brother}}, {{cog|nl|boef||rogue, knave}}, {{cog|de|Bube}} {{gloss|"boy; knave; jack"; > English {{m|en|bub}}}}, {{cog|is|bófi||rogue, crook, bandit, knave}}. See also {{m|en|bully}}.

